Last updated: 29.12.2025

Vibe Day ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your personal information is collected, used, and disclosed by Vibe Day.

This Privacy Policy applies to our website, and its associated subdomains (collectively, our "Service") alongside our application, Vibe Day. By accessing or using our Service, you signify that you have read, understood, and agree to our collection, storage, use, and disclosure of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service.

1. Information We Collect
A. Personal Information When you sign in using Apple Sign-In and Google Sign-In, we collect basic profile information provided by these providers, which may include:

Email address

Display name

Profile picture URL

We use Supabase to securely store this authentication data.

B. Location Data Our application is location-based. We collect your real-time geolocation data (latitude and longitude) to:

Find nearby venues, restaurants, and activities.

Generate AI-powered travel routes and itineraries.

Show events occurring near you (via Ticketmaster).

Calculate travel times and distances.

You can enable or disable location services when you use our Service at any time, through your device settings.

C. Usage Data & Preferences We collect data on how you interact with the app to improve the AI recommendations, including:

Vibe Preferences: Your selected mood, budget, and social setting.

Saved Data: Routes and favorite places you explicitly save.

Search History: Tags and locations you search for within the app.

D. Device Information We may collect specific information about your mobile device when you access our Service to ensure app stability and compatibility. This includes:

Hardware model

Operating system and version (e.g., iOS 17, Android 14)

Unique device identifiers

Mobile network information

Crash reports and system logs (via Google Firebase Crashlytics)

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect in various ways, including to:

Provide, operate, and maintain our application.

Generate AI Content: We send anonymized location and preference data to Google Gemini (AI Service) to generate personalized route descriptions and venue recommendations.

Show Relevant Ads: We use Google AdMob to display rewarded videos, interstitial ads, and banner ads.

Process Transactions: Manage your "Credits" and subscription status (Free/Plus/Pro). Please note that we do not process or store your financial information (e.g., credit card details). All payment transactions are handled securely by the Apple App Store or Google Play Store.

Send Notifications: Send you push notifications regarding updates, security alerts, and relevant travel suggestions (if you have opted in).

Improve, personalize, and expand our application based on user feedback and crash reports.

3. Third-Party Services
We may share information with third-party vendors and service providers that perform services on our behalf. The key third-party services we use include:

Google Firebase (Crashlytics & Analytics): Used to monitor the stability of the application, analyze crash reports, and understand user engagement to improve the user experience.

Google AdMob: Used to display advertisements. AdMob may use identifiers (like Android Advertising ID or IDFA) to show personalized ads.

Google Gemini API: Used to process your preferences and location to generate travel itineraries.

Supabase: Used for database management, authentication, and secure storage.

Google Places API: Used to fetch details about venues and locations.

Ticketmaster API: Used to fetch event data.

Apple Sign-In: Used for authentication purposes on iOS devices.

4. Data Retention and Deletion
We keep your information only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy.

Account Deletion: You have the right to delete your account and all associated data at any time. You can do this directly within the app by going to Profile > Settings > Delete Account. This action is irreversible and will remove your user data, favorites, saved routes, and credits from our database.

5. Security of Your Information
We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your personal information. While we have taken reasonable steps to secure the personal information you provide to us, please be aware that despite our efforts, no security measures are perfect or impenetrable, and no method of data transmission can be guaranteed against any interception or other type of misuse.

6. Children's Privacy
We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected Personal Data from a child under the age of 13 without verification of parental consent, we take steps to remove that information from our servers.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at:

Email: vibedayorj@gmail.com
